definition.value: This is an AE which is a complex, fatiguing, long-term medical condition diagnosed by required primary symptoms and criteria, and often involves a broad range of symptoms.
This is an AE which is a condition in which people in a building suffer from symptoms of illness or become infected with chronic disease from the building in which they work or reside.
This is an AE which is generally a long-term disorder that causes a strong urge to move one's legs.
This is an AE which is a rare X-linked dominant genetic disorder that affects the skin, hair, teeth, nails and central nervous system.
This is an AE which is a neurological disorder causing a range of symptoms due to ischemia in the lateral part of the medulla oblongata in the brainstem.
This is an AE which is a hereditary autoinflammatory syndrome caused by mutations in the mevalonate kinase gene.
This is an AE which is a heterogeneous group of immune disorders.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder characterized by mild-to-moderate intellectual disability.

This is an AE which is a clustering of at least three of the following five medical conditions: abdominal obesity, high blood pressure, high blood sugar, high serum triglycerides, and low serum high-density lipoprotein (HDL).
This is an AE which is a medical condition characterized by a snapping sensation felt when the hip is flexed and extended.
This is an AE which is a syndrome caused by a microdeletion on the long arm of chromosome 22.
This is an AE which is a congenital rare type of strabismus most commonly characterized by the inability of the eye to move outward.

This is an AE which is part of a group called Ras/MAPK pathway syndromes, is a rare autosomal dominant,multisystem disease caused by a mutation in the protein tyrosine phosphatase, non-receptor type 11 gene (PTPN11).
This is an AE which is altered organ function in an acutely ill patient requiring medical intervention to achieve homeostasis.
This is an AE which is an informal label that physicians apply to patients with symptoms similar to those of asthma.
This is an AE which is a compression neuropathy and painful foot condition in which the tibial nerve is compressed as it travels through the tarsal tunnel.
This is an AE which is a rare syndrome caused by a genetic disorder.

This is an AE which is a long-term autoimmune disease that affects the body's moisture-producing (lacrimal and salivary) glands, and often seriously affects other organ systems, such as the lungs, kidneys, and nervous system.
This is an AE which is a complication of otitis media and mastoiditis involving the apex of the petrous temporal bone.
This is an AE which is a chronic and multi-symptomatic disorder affecting returning military veterans of the 1990â€“1991 Persian Gulf War.
This is an AE which is the sensation that an amputated or missing limb is still attached.
This is an AE which is a combination of symptoms that arises when a group of nerves known as the sympathetic trunk is damaged.
This is an AE which is a medical condition of decreased mobility due to disorders of the locomotor system.
This is an AE which is a mild liver disorder in which the liver does not properly process bilirubin.
This is an AE which is a syndrome involving tendonitis (inflammation of tendons) of the rotator cuff muscles as they pass through the subacromial space, the passage beneath the acromion.
This is an AE which is the group of symptoms that occur upon the abrupt discontinuation or decrease in the intake of medicational or recreational drugs.
This is an AE which is an autoimmune disease associated with interstitial lung disease, dermatomyositis, and polymyositis.
This is an AE which is an autoimmune, hypercoagulable state caused by antiphospholipid antibodies.
This is an AE which is a collection of signs and symptoms due to prolonged exposure to glucocorticoids such as cortisol.
This is an AE which is a rapidly worsening brain disease.

This is an AE which is a group of rare, heterogeneous autoinflammatory disease characterized by interleukin 1Î²-mediated systemic inflammation and clinical symptoms involving skin, joints, central nervous system, and eyes.

This is an AE which is a rare progressive disorder of presumed autoimmune cause, characterized by painful muscle spasms, alopecia, diarrhea, endocrinopathy with amenorrhoea and secondary skeletal abnormalities.
This is an AE which is a clinical situation of an individual's first neurological episode, caused by inflammation or demyelination of nerve tissue.

This is an AE which mostly occurs in congenital ptosis patients, is characterized by jaw movement evoking ptotic eyelid retraction, followed by collapse. Inverted, bilateral and acquired MGS were also reported.
This is an AE which is the triad of ascites, pleural effusion, and benign ovarian tumor (ovarian fibroma, fibrothecoma, Brenner tumour, and occasionally granulosa cell tumour).
This is an AE which is a form of chemical pneumonitis or aspiration pneumonitis caused by aspiration of stomach contents (principally gastric acid) during anaesthesia in childbirth.
This is an AE which is one of the family of mitochondrial diseases, which also include MERRF syndrome, and Leber's hereditary optic neuropathy.
This is an AE which is a rare variant of Guillain-BarrÃ©'s syndrome characterized by the acute development of ataxia, ophthalmoparesis, and areflexia.

This is an AE which is an umbrella term covering pain and dysfunction of the muscles of mastication (the muscles that move the jaw) and the temporomandibular joints (the joints which connect the mandible to the skull).
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder that may present with mildly unusual facial features, short height, congenital heart disease, bleeding problems, and skeletal malformations.
This is an AE which is a congenital defect observed in humans which is characterized by facial abnormalities.
This is an AE which is a common and important problem among health professionals that also has adverse effects on people's daily life, especially increasing the incidence of infection and trauma.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder caused by a loss of function of specific genes on chromosome 15.
This is an AE which is a rare condition that encompasses a combination of syndromes such as bronchiectasis, rhinosinusitis and reduced male fertility.
This is an AE which occurs when food, especially sugar, moves too quickly from the stomach to the duodenumâ€”the first part of the small intestineâ€”in the upper gastrointestinal (GI) tract.

This is an AE which refers to as calcium-alkali syndrome, is the third most common cause of hypercalcemia and is characterized by elevated blood calcium levels, metabolic alkalosis, and acute kidney injury.
This is an AE which is a form of inflammatory arthritis that develops in response to an infection in another part of the body (cross-reactivity).
This is an AE which is an eponymous paediatric medical disorder, characterised by gastrointestinal symptoms and associated neurological features.
This is an AE which is a rare headache disorder that belongs to the group of headaches called trigeminal autonomic cephalalgia (TACs).
This is an AE which is the term used for both central pontine myelinolysis and extrapontine myelinolysis.
